@{par}    @{fg fill}A. Demetriades,
@{par}    A. Berkeley,
@{par}    M. Janota Bzowski,
@{par}    S. Pickford,
@{par}    G. Walker,
@{par}    M. Johnson,
@{par}    F. Capone.@{fg text}
@{par}
@{par}Consultants:
@{par}    @{fg fill}M. Fox THE TAVISTOCK CLINIC,
@{par}    M. Martin LEGAL ADVISER,
@{par}    A. Heywood A.C.A,
@{par}    S. Kasabova CAMDEN L.E.A.@{fg text}
@{par}
@{par}    The address is up there, so go on, donate!
@{par}    If you think you can offer something other than money, write!
@{par}
@{par}    I want to say a huge thanks to anyone who does donate some money.
@{par}
@{par}    Thanks for at least reading this... and sorry for any mistakes in
@{par}    the above text - my typing can go a bit haywire sometimes!!

@ENDNODE
@NODE Intro "CDOpus - Introduction"

@{par}CDOpus was originally based on the @{fg shine}CDO.dopus5@{fg text} and @{fg shine}OCD.dopus5@{fg text} ARexx scripts
which @{" I " LINK Credits} wrote a while ago. I wrote it in order to develop my routines for
talking to ARexx ports via Assembler, but since then it has actually grown
in to something quite useful!
@{par}
@{par}@{u}Basically@{uu}, the program has three functions which are intended to
make moving between Shell and @{fg shine}Directory Opus@{fg text} quicker and easier:
@{par}
@{par}@{fg fill}1)@{fg text} You can run it from a Shell to change-directories to the same path as
@{par}   your Directory Opus 5 source lister.
@{par}@{fg fill}2)@{fg text} You can run it from a Shell and have a new DOpus lister open with the
@{par}   same path as your shell. (You can also read into a lister which is
@{par}   already open).
@{par}@{fg fill}3)@{fg text} You can cause DOpus to perform one of its commands on some of the
@{par}   files in the current directory.
@{fg shine}...did I say three? I meant four...@{fg text}
@{par}@{fg fill}4)@{fg text} You can also use it as a command to open listers with given paths, positions
   and modes for when the internal ScanDir command doesn't offer you enough.
@{fg shine}...I didn't expect some kind of Spanish Inquisition...@{fg text}
@{par}@{fg fill}5)@{fg text} Finally, you can set local and global environment variables to lister
   paths for use in scripts.
@{par}
@{par}Read the @{" usage " LINK Usage} node to see exactly what it can do.

@ENDNODE
@NODE Requirements "CDOpus - Requirements"

@{par}See also: @{" Known Bugs " LINK Future}
@{par}
@{par}This program should run on any Amiga with AmigaOS 2 or above.
@{par}
@{par}Of course, you also need @{fg shine}Directory Opus 5@{fg text} (version @{b}5.5@{ub} or above).
@{par}
@{par}This @{fg fill}AmigaGuide@{fg text} takes advantage of some of the extra features of the
@{fg fill}OS3.1 amigaguide.datatype@{fg text}, such as @{fg fill}SmartWrap@{fg text}, @{fg fill}WordWrap@{fg text}, @{fg fill}Colour@{fg text}, and @{fg fill}Styles@{fg text}.
@{fg fill}OS3.0@{fg text} users should get everything apart from the @{fg fill}SmartWrapping@{fg text}, and @{fg fill}OS2@{fg text} 
users should still see the same text, just not as @{bg shine}p@{bg fill}r@{bg shine}e@{bg fill}t@{bg shine}t@{bg fill}y@{bg back}.

@ENDNODE
