@NODE "CheckGuide" "CheckGuide by Eddy Carroll"

@{par}          @{fg shine}CheckGuide 1.0 -- Checks AmigaGuide files for common errors
@{par}
@{par}             by Eddy Carroll, September 1994. Freely distributable.@{fg text}
@{par}
@{par}Introduction
@{par}
@{par}If you've ever tried creating even a modestly sized AmigaGuide file by hand,
@{par}you'll have discovered that it can be quite difficult to keep track of all the
@{par}various links and cross references. As your help file gets larger, it gets
@{par}increasingly harder to ensure that you have remembered to reference all the
@{par}nodes in the file from at least one place, and haven't left any unresolved
@{par}links.
@{par}
@{par}CheckGuide is a simple utility that can detect several common errors in
@{par}AmigaGuide files. The errors it can detect are:
@{par}
@{par}· Extra plain text between an \@ENDNODE and \@NODE (AmigaGuide won't allow such
@{par}  text to ever be displayed)
@{par}
@{par}· Nodes that are defined but not referenced from any other node. Unless your
@{par}  program directly instructs AmigaGuide to access such nodes, the user won't
@{par}  easily be able to access them.
@{par}
@{par}· Links to help nodes that aren't defined within the file.
@{par}
@{par}· Open braces with no preceding \@ character (usually a simple typo).
@{par}
@{par}· \@{" Button "} constructs with no LINK command (an easy mistake to make if
@{par}  you're entering a lot of them).
@{par}
@{par}All of these options can be selectively enabled or disabled.
@{par}
@{par}        @{fg shine}CheckGuide was used in the creation of @{b}THIS@{ub} document!@{fg text}

@ENDNODE
@NODE Installation "CDOpus - Installation"

@{par}See also: @{" Usage " LINK Usage}
@{par}          @{" Examples " LINK Examples}
@{par}
@{par}@{b}NOTE:@{ub} This is just a @{u}suggestion@{uu} of how to install it. You can do with it
@{par}      what you want, and indeed the program can do @{u}many@{uu} more things than
@{par}      the two things which we'll set-up here.
@{par}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} Make sure the @{fg fill}"P"@{fg text} bit is set as this program is @{fg shine}'Pure'@{fg text} and may be made
@{par}  @{b}resident@{ub} @{fg fill}(see below)@{fg text}.
@{par}@{fg fill}>@{fg text} @{bg fill} Protect CDOpus +P @{bg back}
@{par}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} Copy the main file to @{fg fill}DOpus5:c/@{fg text}
@{par}@{fg fill}>@{fg text} @{bg fill} Copy CDOpus DOpus5:c/ @{bg back}
@{par}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} Copy the AmigaGuide to @{fg fill}DOpus5:Help/@{fg text}
@{par}@{fg fill}>@{fg text} @{bg fill} Copy CDOpus.guide DOpus5:Help/ @{bg back}
@{par}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} Setup a @{fg shine}"CDO"@{fg text} alias in your shell to CD to the source lister's directory.
@{par}  (Add this to your @{fg fill}S:Shell-Startup@{fg text})
@{par}@{fg fill}>@{fg text} @{bg fill} Alias CDO "DOpus5:c/CDOpus" @{bg back}
@{par}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} Setup an @{fg shine}"OCD"@{fg text} alias in your shell to open a new lister in your current dir.
@{par}  (Add this to your @{fg fill}S:Shell-Startup@{fg text})
@{par}@{fg fill}>@{fg text} @{bg fill} Alias OCD "DOpus5:c/CDOpus Open" @{bg back}
@{par}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} Read the @{" usage " LINK Usage} and @{" examples " LINK Examples} sections to see what else you can do!
@{par}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} If you want to make the command @{b}resident@{ub} (to save loading time), add this
@{par}  line to your @{fg fill}S:User-Startup@{fg text}...
@{par}@{fg fill}>@{fg text} @{bg fill} Resident DOpus5:c/CDOpus @{bg back}
@{par}  ...and change all the alias commands to reference @{fg fill}"CDOpus"@{fg text} instead of
@{par}  @{fg fill}"DOpus5:c/CDOpus"@{fg text}.

@ENDNODE
@NODE Usage "CDOpus - Usage"

@{par}See also: @{" Installation " LINK Installation}
@{par}          @{" Examples " LINK Examples}
@{par}
@{par}The @{fg fill}CDOpus@{fg text} command takes the following command-line parameters:
@{par}
@{par}@{fg shine}Generic:@{fg text}
@{par} @{" RexxPort  " LINK U_RexxPort}  Specify a differnt port instead of @{fg shine}"DOPUS.1"@{fg text}.
@{par} @{" Help      " LINK U_Help}  @{fg fill}Switch:@{fg text} Brings up this text.
@{par}@{fg shine}Modes:@{fg text}
@{par} @{" <DEFAULT> " LINK U_CD }  CD to 'source' lister's path.
@{par} @{" Open      " LINK U_Open}  @{fg fill}Switch:@{fg text} Read path into a lister.
@{par} @{" Action    " LINK U_Action}  @{fg fill}Switch:@{fg text} Read path into new source lister.
@{par} @{" SetVar    " LINK U_SetVar}  @{fg fill}Switch:@{fg text} Set environment variable.
@{par}@{fg shine}CD mode only:@{fg text}
@{par} @{" Quiet     " LINK U_Quiet}  @{fg fill}Switch:@{fg text} Don't echo the new path to the shell.
@{par}@{fg shine}Open/Action modes only:@{fg text}
@{par} @{" NoFront   " LINK U_NoFront}  @{fg fill}Switch:@{fg text} Don't pop the DOpus screen to front.
@{par} @{" Dir       " LINK U_Dir}  Specify a different directory to read, instead of <CD>.
@{par} @{" Pos       " LINK U_Pos}  Specify different lister position in x/y/w/h format.
@{par}@{fg shine}Open/SetVar modes only:@{fg text} (Open defaults to a new lister)
@{par} @{" Source    " LINK U_SourceDestLock}  @{fg fill}Switch:@{fg text} Read to/from 'source' lister.
@{par} @{" Dest      " LINK U_SourceDestLock}  @{fg fill}Switch:@{fg text} Read to/from 'destination' lister.
@{par}@{fg shine}Open mode only:@{fg text}
@{par} @{" New       " LINK U_New}  @{fg fill}Switch:@{fg text} Force new lister (source/dest/off).
@{par} @{" Lock      " LINK U_SourceDestLock}  @{fg fill}Switch:@{fg text} Lock new lister as source/dest.
@{par}@{fg shine}Action mode only:@{fg text}
@{par} @{" ActPat    " LINK U_ActPat}  Specify files to select.
@{par} @{" ActCom    " LINK U_ActCom}  Specify DOpus5 command to execute.
@{par} @{" ActClose  " LINK U_ActClose}  @{fg fill}Switch:@{fg text} Close lister on completion.
@{par}@{fg shine}SetVar mode only:@{fg text}
@{par} @{" Global    " LINK U_Global}  @{fg fill}Switch:@{fg text} Set global variable instead of local.
@{par}
@{par}@{fg shine}@{u}ReadArgs() Template:@{uu}@{fg text}
@{par}RP=REXXPORT/K, HELP/S, QUIET/S, OPEN/S, ACTION/S, SETVAR/S, DIR=PATH/K,
SOURCE/S, DEST/S, LOCK/S, NEW/S, POS=DIMENSIONS/K, PAT=ACTPAT/K,
COM=ACTCOM/K, ACTCLOSE/S, GLOBAL/S, NOFRONT/S:

@ENDNODE
@NODE U_RexxPort "CDOpus - Usage, RexxPort"

@{par}See also: @{" Examples " LINK Examples}
@{par}
@{par}@{fg fill}RexxPort@{fg text} is an optional @{b}keyword@{ub} which lets you specify the name of the
ARexx port to talk to. By default this is @{fg fill}"DOPUS.1"@{fg text} (most of the time
you'll only be running one copy of DOpus), but should you need to address
another name you can use this.
@{par}
@{par}@{b}NOTE:@{ub} Port names are @{u}case-sensitive@{uu}.
@{par}
@{par}When running @{fg fill}CDOpus@{fg text} from Directory Opus, you should @{u}always@{uu} specify the
Rexx port in case one day you run two copies. To do this you should have...
@{par}@{fg fill}>@{fg text} @{bg fill} ... RexxPort {Qp} ... @{bg back}
@{par}...on the command-line.

@ENDNODE
@NODE U_Help "CDOpus - Usage, Help"

@{par}Seel also: @{" Future " LINK Future}
@{par}
@{par}@{fg fill}Help@{fg text} is a @{b}switch@{ub} which will dump the help-text to the shell window when
given.

@ENDNODE
@NODE U_CD "CDOpus - Usage, CD Mode"

@{par}See also: @{" Usage " LINK Usage}
@{par}          @{" Examples " LINK Examples}
@{par}          @{" Quiet " LINK U_Quiet}
@{par}
@{par}@{fg shine}@{u}CD Mode@{fg text}@{uu}
@{par}
@{par}This is the @{b}default@{ub} mode and is used whenever none of the others are
specified. In @{fg fill}CD Mode@{fg text} the program will attempt to change your shell's
current directory to that of the DOpus 'source' lister.
@{par}
@{par}In this mode, all error messages go to the shell window, while in all other
modes error messages appear in @{b}requesters@{ub}.
@{par}
@{par}Unless you give the @{" Quiet " LINK U_Quiet} switch the new directory path is echoed to the
shell.

@ENDNODE
@NODE U_Open "CDOpus - Usage, Open Mode"

@{par}See also: @{" Usage " LINK Usage}
@{par}          @{" Examples " LINK Examples}
@{par}          @{" NoFront " LINK U_NoFront}
@{par}          @{" Dir " LINK U_Dir}
@{par}          @{" Pos " LINK U_Pos}
@{par}          @{" Source / Dest / Lock " LINK U_SourceDestLock}
@{par}          @{" New " LINK U_New}
@{par}
@{par}@{fg shine}@{u}Open Mode@{fg text}@{uu}
@{par}
@{par}Giving the @{fg fill}Open@{fg text} @{b}switch@{ub} puts CDOpus into @{fg fill}Open Mode@{fg text}. This mode is intended
for reading the directory your shell is in into a DOpus lister.
@{par}
@{par}By default, a new lister is created, but if you specify the @{" Source " LINK U_SourceDestLock} or
@{" Dest " LINK U_SourceDestLock} switches CDOpus will attempt to read the path into an existing
lister of the type given. It will still open a new lister if it can't
find an existing one of the correct type.
@{par}
@{par}If you want to open a new lister of a given type you should also give
the @{" New " LINK U_New} switch on the command line, along with any of @{" Source " LINK U_SourceDestLock}, @{" Dest " LINK U_SourceDestLock},
and @{" Lock " LINK U_SourceDestLock}.
@{par}
@{par}You can specify the position for any newly created lister with the @{" Pos " LINK U_Pos}
keyword.
@{par}
@{par}You can read in a different directory with the @{" Dir " LINK U_Dir} keyword.

@ENDNODE
@NODE U_Action "CDOpus - Usage, Action"

@{par}See also: @{" Usage " LINK Usage}
@{par}          @{" Examples " LINK Examples}
@{par}          @{" NoFront " LINK U_NoFront}
@{par}          @{" Dir " LINK U_Dir}
@{par}          @{" Pos " LINK U_Pos}
@{par}          @{" ActPat " LINK U_ActPat}
@{par}          @{" ActCom " LINK U_ActCom}
@{par}          @{" ActClose " LINK U_ActClose}
@{par}
@{par}@{fg shine}@{u}Action Mode@{fg text}@{uu}
@{par}
@{par}This mode is enabled when the @{fg fill}Action@{fg text} @{b}switch@{ub} is given. A new 'source' lister
for the current directory will open and it is possible to give a
@{" file pattern " LINK U_ActPat} and @{" DOpus command " LINK U_ActCom} so that all files matching the pattern
have the command performed on them.
@{par}
@{par}You can act on a different directory using the @{" Dir " LINK U_Dir} keyword, and you
can change the new lister's position using the @{" Pos " LINK U_Pos} keyword.
@{par}
@{par}You don't have to give either the pattern or the command (you could just
select some files, for example, or just issue a command like @{fg shine}"all"@{fg text}), and
you can have the lister @{" close " LINK U_ActClose} automatically once the command has
completed.

@ENDNODE
@NODE U_SetVar "CDOpus - Usage, SetVar"

@{par}See also: @{" Usage " LINK Usage}
@{par}          @{" Examples " LINK Examples}
@{par}          @{" Source / Dest " LINK U_SourceDestLock}
@{par}          @{" Global " LINK U_Global}
@{par}
@{par}@{fg shine}@{u}SetVar Mode@{fg text}@{uu}
@{par}
@{par}When you give the @{fg fill}SetVar@{fg text} @{b}switch@{ub} CDOpus runs in @{fg fill}SetVar Mode@{fg text}. This means that
it gets the path of either the @{" source " LINK U_SourceDestLock} or @{" destination " LINK U_SourceDestLock} lister and sets
the @{fg shine}CDOSource@{fg text} or @{fg shine}CDODest@{fg text} environment variable.
@{par}
@{par}By default the variable is local to the shell you are running in.
You can make the variable available to the entire system with the @{" Global " LINK U_Global}
switch.
@{par}
@{par}If you don't know what environment variables are you should look them
up in a good AmigaOS manual. @{fg shine}:-)@{fg text}.

@ENDNODE
@NODE U_Quiet "CDOpus - Usage, Quiet"

@{par}Normally, in @{" CD Mode " LINK U_CD}, the name of the new path is echoed to the shell
before the actual directory change takes place. If the @{fg fill}Quiet@{fg text} @{b}switch@{ub} is
given this doesn't happen.

@ENDNODE
@NODE U_NoFront "CDOpus - Usage, NoFront"

@{par}Normally, when in @{" Open Mode " LINK U_Open} or @{" Action Mode " LINK U_Action} the DOpus screen is popped
to the front. If you specify the @{fg fill}NoFront@{fg text} @{b}switch@{ub} this doesn't happen.

@ENDNODE
@NODE U_Dir "CDOpus - Usage, Dir"

@{par}By default, when in @{" Open Mode " LINK U_Open} or @{" Action Mode " LINK U_Action} a lister will read in the
current directory of your shell. You can use the @{fg fill}Dir@{fg text} @{b}keyword@{ub} to specify a
different directory to read in.
@{par}
@{par}Amoung other things, this can be used to open listers from DOpus buttons
when you need a little more control than is offered by the internal
ScanDir command.

@ENDNODE
@NODE U_Pos "CDOpus - Usage, Pos"

@{par}By default, new listers created by CDOpus open under your mouse
pointer with the default size or that snapshotted to the path.
@{par}
@{par}The @{fg fill}Pos@{fg text} @{b}keyword@{ub} can be used to set a different size and/or position for
new listers openned by @{" Open " LINK U_Open} or @{" Action " LINK U_Action}.
@{par}
@{par}The format is @{fg fill}<x-pos>@{fg text}/@{fg fill}<y-pos>@{fg text}/@{fg fill}<width>@{fg text}/@{fg fill}<height>@{fg text}, e.g. 50/10/100/200
@{par}
@{par}@{b}NOTE: @{ub}Specifying -1/-1/@{fg fill}<w>@{fg text}/@{fg fill}<h>@{fg text} will make the lister open under the mouse.

@ENDNODE
@NODE U_SourceDestLock "CDOpus - Usage, Source/Dest/Lock"

@{par}@{u}@{fg shine}The Source, Dest, and Lock Switches@{fg text}@{uu}
@{par}
@{par}The effect of these @{b}switches@{ub} varies depending on what mode you are in:
@{par}
@{par}In @{" Open Mode " LINK U_Open} the @{fg fill}source@{fg text} switch tells CDOpus that you want to read the
directory into the 'source' lister instead of a new one. A new lister will
still be created if no source one is found.
@{par}
@{par}If you give the @{" New " LINK U_New} switch as well as the @{fg fill}Source@{fg text} one in @{" Open Mode " LINK U_Open}
CDOpus will open a new lister for your path and put it in 'source'
mode. If you also give the @{fg fill}Lock@{fg text} switch the lister will be locked in
source mode.
@{par}
@{par}In @{" Open Mode " LINK U_Open} the @{fg fill}Dest@{fg text} switch acts just like the @{fg fill}Source one@{fg text}, with a
few obvious differences.
@{par}
@{par}
@{par}In @{" SetVar Mode " LINK U_SetVar} the @{fg fill}Source@{fg text} switch tells CDOpus to set the @{fg shine}CDOSource@{fg text}
environment variable to the path of the 'source' lister. The @{fg fill}Dest@{fg text} switch
sets the @{fg shine}CDODest@{fg text} variable to the path of the 'destination' lister.

@ENDNODE
@NODE U_New "CDOpus - Usage, New"

@{par}When in @{" Open Mode " LINK U_Open} the @{fg fill}New@{fg text} @{b}switch@{ub} tells CDOpus that it must create a new
lister and put it into the mode given by the @{" source, dest, and lock " LINK U_SourceDestLock}
switches.

@ENDNODE
@NODE U_ActPat "CDOpus - Usage, ActPat"

@{par}Listers openned in @{" Action Mode " LINK U_Action} can have some or all of their files
selected by giving any valid AmigaDOS pattern to the @{fg fill}ActPat@{fg text} @{b}keyword@{ub}.
Note that the @{fg fill}ActPat@{fg text} keyword is entirely @{i}optional @{ui}-- you can execute a
DOpus @{" command " LINK U_ActCom} without selecting any files.

@ENDNODE
@NODE U_ActCom "CDOpus - Usage, ActCom"

@{par}When in @{" Action-mode " LINK U_Action}, the @{fg fill}ActCom@{fg text} keyword takes the name of one of
the internal DOpus commands (you know -- "@{fg fill}Delete@{fg text}", "@{fg fill}All@{fg text}", "@{fg fill}SmartRead@{fg text}", and
so on). The newly created lister will be in 'source' mode, and the command
will be executed @{b}after@{ub} file selection (if any) by the @{" ActPat " LINK U_ActPat} keyword.
@{par}
@{par}For commands like "@{fg fill}Delete@{fg text}" and "@{fg fill}SmartRead@{fg text}" you will want to select some
files first, but for other commands such as "@{fg fill}All@{fg text}" and "@{fg fill}CacheList@{fg text}" there
is no need. Like the @{" ActPat " LINK U_ActPat} keyword, @{fg fill}ActCom@{fg text} is entirely @{i}optional @{ui}--
you can open a lister and select some files without having to execute
a command.

@ENDNODE
@NODE U_ActClose "CDOpus - Usage, ActClose"

@{par}When CDOpus is in @{" Action-mode " LINK U_Action}, the @{fg fill}ActClose@{fg text} @{b}switch@{ub} causes it to
close the new lister automatically once the @{" file selection " LINK U_ActPat} and @{" command " LINK U_ActCom} 
have completed.

@ENDNODE
@NODE U_Global "CDOpus - Usage, Global"

@{par}By default, environment variables created in @{" SetVar Mode " LINK U_SetVar} are @{b}local@{ub},
meaning they only exist for programs run from the same shell. The @{fg fill}Global@{fg text} 
@{b}switch@{ub} causes CDOpus to create @{b}global@{ub} variables instead (stored in @{fg shine}ENV:@{fg text}
with all versions of AmigaDOS upto 3.1) which are available to all
programs running on the machine.
@{par}
@{par}If you don't understand what all this means, it probably isn't of much
use to you anyway.

@ENDNODE
@NODE Examples "CDOpus - Examples"

@{par}See also: @{" Usage " LINK Usage}
@{par}
@{par}Here are some quick examples of how to use the program:
@{par}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} Shell Alias to CD to the @{fg fill}'source'@{fg text} lister's path.
@{par}@{fg fill}>@{fg text} @{bg fill} Alias CDO "DOpus5:c/CDOpus" @{bg back}
@{par}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} Shell Alias to CD to the @{fg fill}'source'@{fg text} lister's path, for a @{b}second@{ub} @{fg fill}DOpus5@{fg text}.
@{par}@{fg fill}>@{fg text} @{bg fill} Alias CDO2 "DOpus5:c/CDOpus RexxPort DOPUS.2" @{bg back}
@{par}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} Shell Alias to open a @{b}new@{ub} lister with the same path as the shell.
@{par}@{fg fill}>@{fg text} @{bg fill} Alias OCD "DOpus5:c/CDOpus Open" @{bg back}
@{par}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} @{b}As above@{ub}, but make it the @{fg fill}'dest'@{fg text} lister as well.
@{par}@{fg fill}>@{fg text} @{bg fill} Alias OCDest "DOpus5:c/CDOpus Open New Dest" @{bg back}
@{par}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} Shell Alias to read the current directory into the @{fg fill}'source'@{fg text} lister.
@{par}@{fg fill}>@{fg text} @{bg fill} Alias Source "DOpus5:c/CDOpus Open Source" @{bg back}
@{par}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} DOpus button to open a @{fg fill}'source'@{fg text} lister in @{fg fill}"RAM:Env"@{fg text}, with given @{fg fill}size@{fg text}.
@{par}@{fg fill}>@{fg text} @{bg fill} AmigaDOS @{bg back}
@{par}@{fg fill}>@{fg text} @{bg fill} DOpus5:c/CDOpus RexxPort {Qp} Open New Source Dir RAM:Env Pos 11/3/100/50 @{bg back}
@{par}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} Shell Alias to have @{fg fill}DOpus@{fg text} @{b}HexRead #?.exe@{ub} in the @{fg fill}current dir@{fg text}.
@{par}@{fg fill}>@{fg text} @{bg fill} Alias HexRead "DOpus5:c/CDOpus Action ActPat #?.exe ActCom HexRead" @{bg back}
@{par}
@{par}@{fg shine}Hope you get the idea!?@{fg text}

@ENDNODE
@NODE History "CDOpus - History"

@{par}See also: @{" Future " LINK Future}
@{par}
@{par}@{b}NOTE:@{ub} Version numbering is in the @{fg shine}<version>@{fg fill}.@{fg shine}<revision>@{fg text} format. This means
@{par}      that version @{fg shine}1.10 @{fg text}(one.ten) is @{b}newer@{ub} than version @{fg shine}1.2 @{fg text}(one.two).
@{par}
@{par}@{u}@{fg shine} v1.1 (Private release) - ??-Aug-1995 @{uu}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} @{b}First@{ub} release for testing.
@{par}
@{par}@{u}@{fg shine} v1.2 (Private release) - 16-Aug-1995 @{uu}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} Reorganised a lot of the code.
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} Added @{" Source " LINK U_SourceDestLock}, @{" Dest " LINK U_SourceDestLock} and, @{" Lock " LINK U_SourceDestLock} @{b}switches@{ub}.
@{par}
@{par}@{u}@{fg shine} v1.3 (Private release) - 19-Aug-1995 @{uu}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} More code reorganisation.
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} Removed @{fg fill}"Reqs"@{fg text} switch - @{b}requesters@{ub} are turned on @{u}automatically@{uu} unless
@{par}  in @{fg fill}CD-mode@{fg text} where error messages go to the @{b}shell@{ub}.
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} Added @{bg fill} ReadSource @{bg back} and, @{bg fill} ReadDest @{bg back} @{b}switches@{ub}.
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} W@{fg fill}r@{fg shine}o@{fg fill}t@{fg text}e @{bg fill}t@{bg shine}h@{bg fill}i@{bg shine}s@{bg back} @{b}A@{ub}@{u}m@{uu}@{b}i@{ub}@{u}g@{uu}@{b}a@{ub}@{u}G@{uu}@{b}u@{ub}@{u}i@{uu}@{b}d@{ub}@{u}e@{uu}.
@{par}
@{par}@{fg shine}@{u} v1.4 (Private release) - 21-Aug-1995 @{uu}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} @{b}Fixed@{ub} a few minor mistakes in the AmigaGuide, added a couple more links
@{par}  and a little more colour in places. Updated the @{" Credits " LINK Credits} node.
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} @{b}Fixed@{ub} something in the way that @{fg fill}ARexx@{fg text} messages are sent to @{fg fill}DOpus5@{fg text}.
@{par}  (This shouldn't have caused any problems, but it is done properly now).
@{par}
@{par}@{u}@{fg shine} v1.5 (Private release) - 27-Aug-1995 @{uu}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} @{b}Added@{ub} my @{b}new@{ub} @{fg fill}email address@{fg text} to the @{" credits " LINK Credits} node.
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} @{b}Added@{ub} an @{fg fill}icon@{fg text} for this 'guide. (@{" Thanks Trevor! " LINK Credits})
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} @{b}Fixed@{ub} alphabetical-sorting in the @{" credits " LINK Credits} node. (@{" Thanks Trevor! " LINK Credits})
@{par}
@{par}@{u}@{fg shine} v1.6 (MWB_DOpus_7.lha release) - 10-Sep-1995 @{uu}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} @{i}Where useful, @{ui}new listers will open @{b}automatically@{ub} if there isn't a lister
@{par}  of the required type open already (just like @{fg fill}DOpus5's@{fg text} internal commands).
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} @{b}Added@{ub} @{bg fill} NoNew @{bg back} @{b}switch@{ub} to disable the above feature.
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} Added a new @{" known bug " LINK Future}, which isn't my fault. :)
@{par}
@{par}@{u}@{fg shine} v1.7 - 6-Jan-1996 @{uu}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} @{b}Added@{ub} @{bg fill} VarSource @{bg back} and @{bg fill} VarDest @{bg back} commands and accompanying @{" Global " LINK U_Global} switch.
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} @{b}Added@{ub} @{" DoAction " LINK U_Action} command and accompanying switches @{" ActPat " LINK U_ActPat}, @{" ActCom " LINK U_ActCom}, and
@{par}  @{" ActClose " LINK U_ActClose}. @{" Thanks " LINK Credits} to Dave Clarke for the suggestion.
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} @{b}Rearranged@{ub} the @{" Usage " LINK Usage} section a little, hopefully it's better now.
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} @{b}Removed@{ub} section about possible @{fg fill}enforcer hits@{fg text}, they were nothing to
@{par}  do with my programs (YIPEE!).
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} @{b}Updated@{ub} @{" Credits " LINK Credits} section. (Most importantly my @{b}new EMail/WWW addresses@{ub}).
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} @{b}Added@{ub} EMail address and WWW URL for @{" Children of the Storm " LINK COTS_Charity}.
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} This should be the last @{fg fill}DOpusFuncs@{fg text} update before @{fg fill}DOpus 5.5@{fg text} is released.
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} Hey! It's my birthday tomorrow!... :-)
@{par}
@{par}@{u}@{fg shine} v1.8 - 8-Jan-1996 @{uu}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} Now @{b}requires@{ub} (and checks for) @{fg fill}DOpus v5.5@{fg text} or above.
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} Thanks to @{fg fill}DOpus 5.5@{fg text}, you can now open listers in the @{b}top corner@{ub} of the
@{par}  screen, and you can also open them @{" under the mouse " LINK U_Pos}.
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} Error routine returns error strings from @{fg fill}DOpus5.5@{fg text} which could help to explain
@{par}  @{i}why @{ui}something went wrong, not just what went wrong (e.g. "@{i}Could not open
@{par}  a new lister, DOpus Reason: Insufficient memory@{ui}", instead of just
@{par}  "@{i}Could not open a new lister@{ui}").
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} One or two other minor improvements.
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} Debug version no longer included in archive.
@{par}
@{par}@{u}@{fg shine} v1.9 - 26-Apr-1996 @{uu}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} Will no longer open @{b}any@{ub} requesters (from Opus or Intuition) when in
@{par}  @{" CD Mode " LINK U_CD}. All error messages will be diverted to the shell so
@{par}  that you can run CDOpus in your shell-startup without getting an error
@{par}  requester because Opus isn't loaded or you don't have a source lister.
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} Note my new @{" webpage URL " LINK Credits}.
@{par}
@{bg fill}===========================================================================@{bg back}
@{par}
@{par}@{u}@{fg shine} v2.0 - 11-May-1996 @{uu}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} The way the program works has been rationalised some what. Hopefully it's
@{par}  now simpler to use.
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} @{bg fill} DoAction @{bg back} keyword renamed to @{" Action " LINK U_Action}.
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} Much has changed, please read the @{" Usage " LINK Usage} section again.
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} The @{bg fill} Index @{bg back} for this guide is gone. I doubt anyone ever used it for
@{par}  such a small program.
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} Rewrote most of the AmigaGuide.

@Remark VERSION NUMBERS/DATES: VER string and Contents Node.

@ENDNODE
@NODE Future "CDOpus - Future & Known Bugs"

@{par}See also: @{" History " LINK History}
@{par}          @{" Credits " LINK Credits}
@{par}
@{par}@{fg shine}@{u} To Do: @{uu}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} Make the @{" help " LINK U_Help} text pause if the shell window is not tall enough.
@{par}  I'm too lame to be work out how to do it.
@{par}o@{fg shine} Add an option to @{b}automatically load@{ub} @{fg fill}DOpus5@{fg text} if it isn't already loaded.
@{par}  This should be very easy to do but I wouldn't personally use it, so I'll
@{par}  only add it if someone asks for it.
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} If you want something, @{" ask " LINK Credits} for it!
@{par}
@{par}@{fg shine}@{u} Known Bugs: @{uu}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} There is a bug in the OS3.1 AmigaGuide which can cause extra spaces,
@{par}  missing spaces, and duplicated words at line-wraps. @{b}This it not my fault!@{ub}

@ENDNODE
